Order Instructions

Client Order Instructions:

Escalation Contact: appraisaldesk@cfmtg.com

 

NOTE THAT THIS CLIENT NOW ORDERS VIA REGGORA AND ENCOMPASS 

  • WHEN AN ORDER COMES IN IDENTIFY WHICH PLATFORM THEY ORDERED FROM AS IT WILL DETERMINE DIFFERENT FLOWS

 

REGGORA ORDER INSTRUCTIONS

**Payment** - For all orders placed through Reggora, payment will either be collected directly by Reggora or invoiced to Cornerstone. Fastapp will proceed with all Reggora orders upon receipt, regardless of whether a payment confirmation from Reggora is visible.

 

Reggora Payment Payment Comment: 

  1. Payment in Reggora: The fees are collected in Reggora before it gets to Fastapps system. If an order hasnt been paid, Reggora will not release it to Fastapp.
  2. Payment Confirmation: Upon order receipt, ensure that the fee matches the amount collected as shown in the payment message from the client.
  3. Completion and Funds Transfer: Payment will transfer to Fastapp once the order milestone ("Inspection Complete" or "Report Complete") is triggered.
  4. No Direct Collection or Refunds: Fastapp is not responsible for collecting payments or issuing refunds for these orders. All refunds and payment-related issues are managed by the client/Reggora.  Escalate to Billy for assistance with any payment related issues.

 

RUSH Fees:

  1. If the client designates an order as a "Rush", we will need to add the rush product to the order and make sure the fee they sent over/collected aligns with what our order shows.
  2. Look at the "Expected Transfer Amount" at the start of the order.  it should show a fee that has been collected and that fee needs to align with our system. You can also look into the appraisal order form under the supporting documents to confirm the fee.

 

Fee Modification Procedure:

  1. Utilize the fee modification tool for any required fee increases. Actions > Send Modification Request
  2. Check off Send Fee Change Request, enter the new fee, place a comment as to why the fee change is happening.
  3. Do not proceed with the appraisal until the new fee is accepted by the client.
  4. Wait for fee collection confirmation. It will come in the form of a system notification, not just client communication.
  5. If you are uncertain if the fee has been collected ask appraisals@PRMG.net for confirmation that the fee has been collected

 

Due Date Modification:

  1. Modify due dates via the Modification tool in the actions tab. Actions > Send Modification Request
  2. Communicate the reason for any changes to the client 
  3. Please note, at any given point in the flow of the order, even if we are having a delay due to the inspection, and the due date needs to be pushed, the modification request must be sent and approved by the client.

 

 

ENCOMPASS PAYMENT INSTRUCTIONS

Send a payment link from Fastapps system to the borrower.

 

 

 

 

Fee Approval

  • No fee approval required from Client if the fee is $750 or less.
  • Do not inflate fees unnecessarily – consistent pricing is being closely monitored.
  • Idaho Only -  as long as the fee is around $800 and tt is 2 wks, they will approve.

 

Purchase Transaction Orders:

  • If payment is not made within 24 hours, change the order to Invoice and assign it to an appraiser.

  • Send the payment link to: appraisaldesk@cfmtg.com so they can attempt to collect payment while the order is in progress.

  • In the comment section of the payment link, include:
    "Payment has not been made in the first 24 hours, sending a payment link to you per your directive."

 

Refinance Transaction Orders:

  • If payment is not made within 24 hours, resend the payment link to appraisaldesk@cfmtg.com.

    • In the comment section of the payment link, include: Payment has not been made in the first 24 hours, sending a payment link to you per your directive.

  • Do not assign until payment is received or the client provides specific instruction.

  • No Refinance order is to be assigned unless payment is collected or the client has explicitly requested to Invoice

 

Due Dates

  • Standard due date is set to 6 business days.

  • If the Rush add-on is selected, the due date is reduced by 3 business days
